	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just started playing a bard, I bought the game two months ago and started as a Ranger on Prexus, now I play on the new PvP diety server as a nuetral bard of the Tribunial, so far I have learned to twist 3 songs quite well, but at lvl 10 I am not to clear on which songs will benefit me the most, I usually am soloing even or yellows to me and I do quite well most of the time losing about 2 bubs health and then sitting with heal song to recover quickly, but what really gets to me is the bashing I take from mobs that disrupts my songs, it seem's that almost every mob can bash and that is very annoying, that is one reason I think a bard should not serve as a tank, what good are you if you can't play your songs, also I don't do very much damage, I am using a fine steel long sword and my 1hs skill is maxed, I have almost 300 ac unbuffed and about 240hp with 90 base str and 80 base stamina as a halfelf, I didn't put any points into any other stat except STR and STM, was this a mistake? is there a way to avoid being bashed? what 3 songs benefit the most at lvl 10?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
