<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99680503091703></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99680503091703><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=99680503091703>RE: Endevor</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=31993><span id=Scholar>Taamas</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>61 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 2nd 10:17 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>heres my advice:<br><br>stat point allocation: you should put at least 10 points into cha at startup - if not its not the end of the world. put 10 more into dex and whatever left into str - cha affects how well we can charm/mez without gettin resisted (very important later on when grps will depend on you since no chanter is available to do crowd control) - dex affects your fizzle rates on songs (very important no matter what) and how often your weps proc - since your a plate wearing class your gonna need str to carry it.<br><br>bashing: only ogres and trolls are immune from bash (from frontside - vulnerable to bash from backside) and we can't have ogre or troll bards. you'll get bashed and bashed alot get used to it lol   =D<br><br>songs: the best songs to chose from at lvl 10 are anthem/warsong - healing hymn - chant of battle. imho those would be best for your lvl<br><br>hope that helps   =D<br><br><br>Taamas Starsinger<br>52nd Minstrel of Saryrn<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
